Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/List/Difference
Synopsis The difference between two lists.
Syntax Exp1 - Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 - Exp2
list[T1] list[T2] list[lub(T1,T2)]
list[T1] T2 list[lub(T1,T2)]
T1 list[T2] list[lub(T1,T2)]
Description If both Exp1 and Exp2 have a list as value, the result is the difference of these two list values. If one of Exp1 or Exp2 does not have a list as value, it is first converted to a list before the difference is computed.
Examples 
rascal>[1, 2, 3, 4] - [1, 2, 3];
